## 'telex-workflow.json'

Save this file in your project root as `telex-workflow.json`.

This is a Telex.im workflow definition that connects directly to your deployed agent endpoint.  
When you deploy your Mastra server (e.g. on Render, Railway, or Vercel), replace the placeholder URL.

```json
{
  "active": true,
  "category": "utilities",
  "description": "A workflow that fetches and summarizes historical events for today or a given date.",
  "id": "today_in_history_workflow",
  "long_description": "The Today in History Agent provides a concise list of notable events for today or any requested date. It uses the Wikipedia 'On This Day' API and Google Gemini for summarization. Commands: 'today' or 'history <month> <day>'.",
  "name": "today_in_history_agent",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "today_in_history_node",
      "name": "Today in History Agent",
      "parameters": {},
      "position": [450, 120],
      "type": "a2a/mastra-a2a-node",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "url": "https://your-deployed-domain.com/a2a/message"
    }
  ],
  "settings": {
    "executionOrder": "v1"
  },
  "short_description": "Fetches daily historical events using Mastra AI Agent"
}
